.TH FOLIO 1 "2026-07-11" "folio 0.9.2rc1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
folio \- AsciiDoc note-taking application
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B folio
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B folio
is a GTK 4 note-taking application. Notes are written in a strict subset of
AsciiDoc and rendered live into a readable page; malformed markup reports a
precise error rather than rendering silently wrong.
.PP
Notes are organised with tags rather than folders, filtered live by a search
box, and saved continuously as you type. Each note can carry file attachments.
.PP
The command takes no options and no arguments; the whole application is driven
from its window. Press
.B F1
in the application for the built-in markup reference.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/folio/notes.db
The note library: a single SQLite database holding every note, tag and
attachment. It is created on first launch, together with a seed welcome note.
Honours
.BR $XDG_DATA_HOME .
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/folio/session.json
Restored window and selection state.
.SH SEE ALSO
The project homepage,
.UR https://github.com/rand-byte/folio
.UE .
